# Privacy Policy

## 1. Introduction and Legal Framework

This Privacy Policy is governed by the Protection of Personal Information Act 4 of 2013 (POPIA) of South Africa, the Electronic Communications and Transactions Act 25 of 2002 (ECTA), and the Consumer Protection Act 68 of 2008 (CPA). As the responsible party under POPIA, UniHelp is committed to processing your personal information lawfully and in a reasonable manner that does not infringe on your privacy rights.

## 2. Definitions

For clarity and in accordance with POPIA:

• "Personal Information" means information relating to an identifiable, living, natural person or juristic person.
• "Processing" means any operation or activity concerning personal information.
• "Responsible Party" refers to UniHelp as the entity determining the purpose and means of processing personal information.
• "Operator" means a person who processes personal information for us in terms of a contract or mandate.
• "Data Subject" refers to you, the user of our educational services.

## 3. Information We Collect

### Personal Information
• Full Name
• Email Address
• Phone Number
• Academic Records
• Identity/Passport Number
• Current Educational Institution
• Academic Interests
• Financial Information (for bursary applications)
• Employment History (for internship applications)

### Educational Information
• Academic transcripts and certificates
• Standardized test scores
• Educational history and qualifications
• Career interests and goals
• Extra-curricular activities
• Letters of recommendation

## 4. How We Use Your Information

We use your information to:

• Process university applications
• Match you with relevant bursary opportunities
• Connect you with student accommodation providers
• Identify suitable internship positions
• Provide personalized educational guidance
• Communicate important updates about your applications

## 5. Information Sharing

We may share your information with:

• Universities and educational institutions
• Bursary providers and sponsors
• Verified accommodation providers
• Potential employers for internships
• Third-party service providers who assist in application processing

All sharing is done with your explicit consent and in compliance with POPIA.

## 6. Data Security

We implement strict security measures to protect your educational and personal information:

• Encrypted data storage and transmission
• Regular security audits
• Access controls and authentication
• Secure backup systems
• Employee confidentiality agreements

## 7. Document Retention

We retain your documents and information:

• Throughout your application processes
• For the duration of your academic program
• As required by educational institutions
• In accordance with legal requirements
• Until you request deletion of your account

## 8. Your Rights

• Access your personal and educational information
• Update or correct your information
• Request deletion of your account and data
• Opt-out of marketing communications
• Object to certain processing activities
• Request data portability

## 9. Third-Party Services

We partner with:

• Educational institutions
• Accommodation providers
• Bursary organizations
• Internship providers

All partners are bound by strict data protection agreements.

## 10. Changes to Privacy Policy

We may update this policy to reflect:

• New features and services
• Legal and regulatory requirements
• Enhanced security measures
• Improved privacy protections

